Common.LongDescription.Common.Text: Rare offering of a manufacturing facility. Located directly across the street is 42 acres of vacant land. The sale of the building is in conjunction with the land sale on Decosta Street of 42 acres ($840,000). This General Industrial Zoned building is just 20 minutes west of Ottawa.The total building area is 173,300 sf, separated by production area (135,000sf), main office area (22,000 sf), maintenance/machine area (7,800 f), Plant Storage Room area (3,200 sf), & electrical shop area (1,150 sf). The outside buildings include garage (2,200 sf), Coverall (6,000), and Quonset Hut (3,000 sf).Services to the building include: Primary voltage of 44,000; secondary voltage of 4,160; Water Supply 6in diameter, 40,000 gallons/hour. The building includes Bridge Cranes: 3 Hepburn (5 tons each), 1 Larco crane (20 tons), 1 Demag (1 ton). The floors of the production area are 10inches thick of 3,500 PSI concrete with 5/8" structural rebar. Multiple dock level doors and drive in doors throughout.

Rare opportunity to buy a 15,200 sq. ft. industrial building in East St. Catharines. Located blocks from QEW highway access and commercial amenities. This building is equipped with a loading dock, gradelevel door, 12 ft. clear height, finished offices, paved on-site parking, and a small data centre. Industrial buildings for sale are a rare find in this market so act quickly. The building is currently finished over 50% office space which can be good for a buyer who needs that, or the offices can be demolished for industrial uses.

Industrial property for sale in St. Catharines with two buildings on site of similar size, totaling approximately 20,000 sq. ft. on 4.10 acres. This unique opportunity could entertain buyers that want both buildings for themselves or one to occupy and one to lease out for investment. The extra acreage could allow for future expansion should a buyer want to develop more than what is currently there. The buildings are equipped with 14 ft. clear height, 3 phase power, loading docks, and grade level door access. This could be an ideal opportunity for ACMPR medical cannabis growers, especially ones with multiple licenses but it can also be used for warehouse, manufacturing, and service uses. The location is close to the QEW for highway access and is close to commercial amenities. Seller wishes to maintain privacy so please do not visit the property without making arrangements first.

Here's your opportunity to own an industrial investment property with highway exposure in the heart of St. Catharines with visibility from theQEW. With St. Catharines being the business hub of the Niagara region this building is well situated with nearby commercial amenities, exposure, and highway access. This building currently has two tenants consisting of a vehicle collision repair centre and a stair maker, and there is plenty of potential upside in rent.

This A class, 53,855 SF former manufacturing facility represents a rare opportunity to acquire a near turnkey property in one of the region’s most desirable industrial parks, Oldcastle Industrial Park. Strategically located minutes from Highway 401, the Property is ideally suited for various automotive, manufacturing and warehousing applications with crane rail capacity up to 40 tons, clear heights up to 30 ft (under truss) and three drive-in doors for access. With roughly 11.8% of nicely appointed office (6,365 SF) and a 3.75 acre site size, the Property offers plenty of growth potential for staffing and operations with excess land for future building expansion up to 16,956 SF or an additional 96 vehicle stalls.

Property offers long-term upside potential while enjoying stable, under-market tenant income.
